          "date": "2014-08-11 15:04:35.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "subject": "LU-XXXX: obd: don't let coh_page_bufsize grow",
        "message": "LU-XXXX: obd: don't let coh_page_bufsize grow\n\nlov_init_raid0 is incrementing coh_page_bufsize with the size of each\nstripe. However when the layout is resized, it starts with the\nprevious, already incremented coh_page_bufsize, adding more to\nit. Eventually, given several layout resize, coh_page_bufsize reaches\n64KiB and overflows back to a small value. At that point the object is\nnot big enough to store the requested data, and this leads to memory\nscribble.\n\nSo reset coh_page_bufsize in lov_delete_raid0.\n\nChange-Id: I0f55664cc761bb8e4d0c714132d46f5e9ea76804\nSigned-off-by: frank zago <fzago@cray.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
  "requirements": [],
  "submit_records": []
